{"name":"Bookshelf.Apostol.Chapter_1_11","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Data.Real.Basic"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L111-L111","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_7b","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_7b","doc":"### Exercise 7b\n\nIf `a` and `b` are positive integers with no common factor, we have the formula\n`Σ_{n=1}^{b-1} ⌊na / b⌋ = ((a - 1)(b - 1)) / 2`. When `b = 1`, the sum on the\nleft is understood to be `0`.\n\nDerive the result analytically as follows: By changing the index of summation,\nnote that `Σ_{n=1}^{b-1} ⌊na / b⌋ = Σ_{n=1}^{b-1} ⌊a(b - n) / b⌋`. Now apply\nExercises 4(a) and (b) to the bracket on the right.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L97-L99","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_5","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_5","doc":"### Exercise 5\n\nThe formulas in Exercises 4(d) and 4(e) suggest a generalization for `⌊nx⌋`.\nState and prove such a generalization.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L88-L90","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4e","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4e","doc":"### Exercise 4e\n\n`⌊3x⌋ = ⌊x⌋ + ⌊x + 1/3⌋ + ⌊x + 2/3⌋`\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L80-L82","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4d","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4d","doc":"### Exercise 4d\n\n`⌊2x⌋ = ⌊x⌋ + ⌊x + 1/2⌋`\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L50-L74","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4c","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4c","doc":"### Exercise 4c\n\n`⌊x + y⌋ = ⌊x⌋ + ⌊y⌋` or `⌊x⌋ + ⌊y⌋ + 1`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L30-L44","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4b_2","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4b_2","doc":"### Exercise 4b.2\n\n`⌊-x⌋ = -⌊x⌋ - 1` otherwise.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L23-L24","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4b_1","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4b_1","doc":"### Exercise 4b.1\n\n`⌊-x⌋ = -⌊x⌋` if `x` is an integer.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/jrpotter/bookshelf/blob/d601793e5e2b35e197310e88f26e6d0ceb03750f/Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.lean#L16-L17","name":"Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4a","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Bookshelf/Apostol/Chapter_1_11.html#Apostol.Chapter_1_11.exercise_4a","doc":"### Exercise 4a\n\n`⌊x + n⌋ = ⌊x⌋ + n` for every integer `n`.\n"}]}